OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1774555873
OL,3,CDoctor caught using dead father's
OL,4,Cdisabled blue badge to park for free
OL,6,FA doctor who used his dead father's
OL,7,Fdisabled blue badge to park for free
OL,8,Fin Reading town centre has been fined.
OL,10,FDr Emir Patel, of Rangeley Place, in
OL,11,Fthe town, was fined #2,477.50 at
OL,12,FReading Crown Court on 17 March 2026.
OL,14,FOn 5 November 2025, council officers
OL,15,Fdiscovered a red Renault vehicle
OL,16,Fparked in a disabled bay at St Mary's
OL,17,FButts displaying a blue badge which
OL,18,Fhad expired on 3 July 2025.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G1/5
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41702
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1774555873
OL,3,CDoctor caught using dead father's
OL,4,Cdisabled blue badge to park for free
OL,6,FFurther investigations found that the
OL,7,Foriginal badge holder, Dr Patel's late
OL,8,Ffather, had passed away and that the
OL,9,Fbadge had actually been cancelled in
OL,10,FApril 2025.
OL,12,FDespite this, Dr Patel had kept it and
OL,13,Fput it on display in the hire car he
OL,14,Fhad collected the same day.
OL,16,FDr Patel pleaded guilty to an offence
OL,17,Funder Section 2 of the Fraud Act 2006
OL,18,F(Fraud by False Representation).
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/5
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,418,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F417A1774555873
OL,3,CDoctor caught using dead father's
OL,4,Cdisabled blue badge to park for free
OL,6,FHe was ordered to pay a #560 fine and
OL,7,F#1917.50 in investigation and legal
OL,8,Fcosts within six months. as well as a
OL,9,Fvictim surcharge of #244.
OL,11,FJohn Ennis, Reading Borough Council's
OL,12,FLead Councillor for Transport, said:
OL,13,F"The disabled persons parking scheme
OL,14,Fis a lifeline for residents who
OL,15,Fgenuinely need it as it allows them to
OL,16,Fpark close to homes or shops.
OL,18,F"The criminal misuse of blue badges
OL,19,Fcompletely undermines the system and
OL,20,Ftakes parking spaces away from those
OL,21,Fwho actually need them.
OL,26,@uD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/5
